###################################################################################################

This to compile the libAlltabs.so into ROOT.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create the dictionary:

rootcint -f alltabsDict.cc -c Nuclide.hh Table.hh LinkDef.h

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compile the shared library:

g++ -Wall -shared -fPIC Table.cc Nuclide.cc alltabsDict.cc -o libAlltabs.so `root-config --cflags --glibs`

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a symbolic link to the ROOT default lib folder to make the libAlltabs.so available system-wide:

ln -s $PWD/libAlltabs.so $ROOTSYS/lib/

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Map the library to libTree.so so that it gets loaded by default

rlibmap -o libAlltabs.rootmap -l libAlltabs.so -d libTree.so -c LinkDef.h

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Move the map file to the ROOT library folder:

mv libAlltabs.rootmap $ROOTSYS/lib/

###################################################################################################

The alltabs2ttree is a code to read and save to a ROOT TTree the alltabs file (ONLY TABLE 4 FOR NOW)
To compile, just copy and paste:

g++ -std=c++11 alltabs2ttree.cc -Wall -g `root-config --cflags --glibs` -L./ -lAlltabs -o alltabs2ttree
